<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="373" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,438,1230]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1094,1119]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has been confused with 
<taxonomicName box="[763,869,1095,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis box="[763,869,1095,1119]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">M. laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be differentiated from the latter by the characters of the male abdomen: 
<number box="[526,540,1134,1158]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373" value="2.0">2</number>
nd acrotergite with trunk horizontal and 
<number box="[984,998,1134,1158]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373" value="2.0">2</number>
nd tergal apodemes with posterior lobes not extending beyond posterior margin of tergite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1276,1205,1230]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,438,1230]" box="[199,1276,1205,1230]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1205,1230]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<emphasis box="[580,630,1206,1230]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">nabi</emphasis>
” is derived from the name of Dr. Kwon’s daughter, Nabi.
</paragraph>
